    "The set T x,P is defined as a thickened affine subspace close to the vector x for coordinates in I P.",
    "If a vector x 0 is in T x,P, then x 0 is close to x for all coordinates in I P, but x 0 may be far away from x for coordinates outside of I P.",
    "Examples of these definitions are given in Supplementary Figs. 1 and 2.",
    "We can now define the feature map ϕ taking an m-dimensional vector x to an m ϕ -dimensional vector ϕ(x) using the thickened affine subspaces T x 0,P for every geometrically local Pauli observable P ∈ S (geo) and every vector x 0 in the discrete lattice X P.",
